---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Car Loan | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Car Loan</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Car Loan</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Drive home your dream car with affordable car loan options from India's leading banks. Enjoy up to 100% on-road price funding, low interest rates, and flexible repayment tenures for new and used cars.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-car"></i> New & Used Cars
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-hand-holding-dollar"></i> Up to 100% Funding
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i> Interest 7.5%+
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>Car Loan Overview</h2>
          <p>A Car Loan enables you to finance the purchase of a new or pre-owned vehicle from banks and NBFCs at competitive interest rates. Most lenders fund up to 90-100% of the on-road price for new cars and 70-85% of the valuation for used cars. The car itself serves as collateral, making it a secured loan with lower interest rates compared to personal loans.</p>
          <p>Car loans are available for all types of passenger vehicles including hatchbacks, sedans, SUVs, MUVs, and luxury cars from any authorized dealer across India. With tenures ranging from 1 to 7 years and minimal documentation, getting a car loan has never been easier. Many lenders also offer pre-approved car loans to existing customers with instant approval.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">7.5%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Interest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹1 Cr</span>
              <span class="info-label">Maximum Loan Amount</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">7 Yrs</span>
              <span class="info-label">Maximum Tenure</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Car Loan Interest Rates 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Max Loan Amount</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>SBI</td>
                <td>8.25% onwards</td>
                <td>₹1 Crore</td>
                <td>7 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Bank</td>
                <td>8.50% onwards</td>
                <td>₹1 Crore</td>
                <td>7 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>8.75% onwards</td>
                <td>₹80 Lakh</td>
                <td>7 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Axis Bank</td>
                <td>8.40% onwards</td>
                <td>₹75 Lakh</td>
                <td>7 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Kotak Mahindra Bank</td>
                <td>8.60% onwards</td>
                <td>₹1 Crore</td>
                <td>7 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>New Car Loan vs Used Car Loan</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>New Car Loan:</strong> Up to 100% of on-road price funded, interest rates from 7.5% p.a., tenure up to 7 years, and minimal documentation with quick disbursal</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Used Car Loan:</strong> Up to 85% of car valuation funded, interest rates from 10% p.a., tenure up to 5 years, and additional vehicle inspection required before approval</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Down Payment:</strong> New cars typically require 0-10% down payment, while used cars require 15-30% depending on the car's age and condition</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Age Limit for Used Cars:</strong> Most banks finance used cars that are not older than 7-8 years at the time of loan application, and the total age at loan maturity should not exceed 10 years</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Insurance:</strong> Comprehensive car insurance is mandatory for both new and used car loans. Many lenders offer bundled insurance at discounted premiums</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Salaried individuals with a minimum monthly income of ₹15,000 and at least 1 year of work experience</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Self-employed individuals with a minimum annual income of ₹2 Lakh and at least 2 years of business continuity</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Age between 21 to 65 years at the time of loan maturity</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> CIBIL score of 700 or above for the best interest rates and quick approval</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Valid driving license is required at the time of vehicle registration</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Apply for a Car Loan</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Choose Your Car</h4>
              <p>Select your preferred car model, variant, and dealer. Get the on-road price quotation from the dealer.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Check Eligibility</h4>
              <p>Use our car loan eligibility calculator to determine your loan amount and compare rates across lenders.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Submit Application</h4>
              <p>Apply online or at the bank branch with required documents. Get instant approval for pre-approved offers.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Drive Home</h4>
              <p>The loan amount is disbursed to the dealer's account directly. Complete registration and drive your new car home.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Identity proof: Aadhaar card, PAN card, passport, or voter ID</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Address proof: Aadhaar, utility bills, passport, or rental agreement</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Income proof: Salary slips (last 3 months) for salaried or ITR (last 2 years) for self-employed</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Bank statements of the last 6 months showing salary credits or business transactions</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Proforma invoice or quotation from the authorized car dealer</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Passport-size photographs (2 copies)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> For used cars: RC book, insurance copy, vehicle inspection report, and transfer documents</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3>Apply for Car Loan</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Car Type</option>
                  <option value="new">New Car</option>
                  <option value="used">Used Car</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Car Value (₹)" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block">Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3>Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/personal-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Personal Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Page CTA -->
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Ready to Drive Home Your Dream Car?</h3>
          <p>Compare car loan offers from India's top banks and get the lowest EMI for your budget.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Talk to Expert <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">FAQs</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Everything you need to know about Car Loans</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I get a car loan with zero down payment? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, several banks including SBI, HDFC, and ICICI offer up to 100% on-road price financing for new cars, which means zero down payment. However, 100% funding is typically available to salaried applicants with a high CIBIL score (750+), stable employment, and a good relationship with the bank. For used cars, a minimum down payment of 15-20% is usually required.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What is the ideal tenure for a car loan? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">The ideal car loan tenure depends on your budget and financial goals. A shorter tenure (3-4 years) results in higher EMIs but lower total interest paid. A longer tenure (5-7 years) gives you lower monthly EMIs but increases the total interest cost significantly. Financial experts generally recommend a tenure of 4-5 years as it balances affordable EMIs with reasonable total interest outgo. Also consider that the car's value depreciates over time, so a very long tenure may result in negative equity.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Is car insurance mandatory for a car loan? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, comprehensive car insurance is mandatory for the entire loan tenure. Since the car serves as collateral, the lender requires insurance to protect the asset. The insurance policy must include a hypothecation clause in favor of the lending bank. While lenders may recommend their partner insurance companies, you are free to choose any IRDAI-approved insurer. The first year's insurance premium is usually included in the on-road price and funded as part of the loan.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I prepay or foreclose my car loan early? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, most banks allow prepayment and foreclosure of car loans. For floating rate car loans, as per RBI guidelines, no prepayment or foreclosure charges can be levied. For fixed rate loans, a nominal charge of 2-5% of the outstanding principal may apply. Prepaying your car loan can save you a significant amount in interest, especially if done within the first half of the loan tenure when the interest component is highest.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I transfer my car loan to another bank for a lower interest rate? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, car loan balance transfer is possible and can save you money if you find a significantly lower interest rate. The new bank will pay off your existing loan, and you continue paying EMIs to the new lender at the reduced rate. However, consider the processing fees, transfer charges, and any foreclosure penalty from the existing bank before making the switch. A balance transfer is generally beneficial if the rate difference is at least 1-2% and there is a substantial remaining tenure.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
